IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TEXAS "J" REGIONAL ADVISORY COUNCIL IS COMPRISED OF HEALTHCARE ENTITIES WHITHIN 17 TEXAS COUNTIES. THE ORGANIZATION IS CHARTERED BY THE TEXAS DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH BUREAU OF EMERGENCY MANAGEMENT TO DEVELOP, IMPLEMENT, AND MONITOR REGIONAL EMERGENCEY SERVICES OR TRAUMA SYSTEM PLANS FOR TRAUMA SERVICE AREA "J; AND TO OVERSEE TRAUMA SYSTEM NETWORKING. PARTICIPANTS IN THE ORGANIZATION ARE HOSPITALS, PHYSICIANS, NURSES, EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICE PROVIDERS, AND OTHER INDIVIDUALS INTERESTED IN TRUAMA CARE LOCATED, PROVIDING SERVICES, OR RESIDING IN TRAUMA SERVICES AREA "J" WHICH/WHO ALSO SATISFIES OTHER REQUIREMENTS OF PARTICIPATION.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE TEXAS "J" REGIONAL ADVISORY COUNCIL SHALL ENCOURAGE AND SUPPORT A COMPREHENSIVE CONTINUM OF QUALITY HEALTH CARE TO BE PROVIDED FOR ALL PATIENTS IN TRAUMA SERVICE ARE "J", WITHOUT REGARD TO RACE, COLOR, CREED, GENDER, NATIONAL ORIGIN, SEXUAL ORIENTATION, GENDER IDENTITY, OR ABILITY TO PAY.
IRS990.Desc: INJURY PREVENTION, EDUCATION, SUPPLY ASSISTANCE BY MAINTAINING A REGIONAL TRAUMA SYSTEM SERVING 17 TEXAS COUNTIES. PROVIDING TRAINING, EQUIPMENT AND OTHER SUPPORT TO FIRE AND EMS UNITS AND AREA HOSPITALS. THE TEXAS "J" REGIONAL ADVISORY COUNCIL SHALL ENCOURAGE AND SUPPORT A COMPREHENSIVE CONTINUUM OF QUALITY HEALTH CARE TO BE PROVIDED FOR ALL PATIENTS IN THE TRAUMA SERVICE AREA "J"

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION APPROVES GRANT FUNDS BASED ON AN APPLICATION PROCESS. ALL GRANTEES ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR FULFILLING THE GRANT REQUIREMENTS, INCLUDING PROVIDING DOCUMENTATION AND RECEIPTS TO THE ORGANIZATION FOR ALL TRAUMA EQUIPMENT AND SUPPLIES PURCHASED WITH GRANT FUNDS. SB 8 THRU DECEMBER 2024 (GRANTS TO INDIVIDUALS): THE ORGANIZATION KEEPS RECORDS FOR EACH STUDENT. THEY REPORT QUARTERLY TO DSHS AND SHARE THEIR FINANCIALS EACH MONTH AT A GENERAL MEMBERSHIP MEETING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD WILL BE PROVIDED A COPY OF THE FORM 990 VIA DROPBOX, AT AN IN PERSON MEETING, AND WILL BE MADE AVAILABLE IN THE OFFICE BEFORE IT IS FILED. A COPY OF THE 990 WILL ALSO BE AVAILABLE ON THE ENTITY WEBSITE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: HIRING IS APPROVED BY THE BOARD AND AN ANNUAL REVIEW IS CONDUCTED BEFORE ANY PAY INCREASES IS APPROVED AFTER COMPARING LOCAL AND REGIONAL COMPENSATION FOR SIMILAR POSITIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES ITS GOVERING DOCUMENTS, CONFILICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE ON A REQUEST BY REQUEST BASIS.
